Five people arrested  in the Michael Brown protests are suing Ferguson police for $40million over claims they were assaulted and brutalised with rubber bullets and tear gas.

St. Louis County and Ferguson officers have been accused of treating US citizens like 'war combatants', including one woman who was assaulted as she went to buy ice-cream.

Thousands of demonstrators have marched in the Missouri city, demanding the arrest of white police officer, Darren Wilson, who shot dead unarmed black teenager, Michael Brown, earlier this month. 

