He fell into a creek or sewer, where officers 'pounced on him, slammed his face into the concrete, and pushed his head into the water to the point that he felt he was going to be drowned'.

Damon Coleman and Theophilus Green claim they were peacefully protesting when police in riot gear fired stun grenades in their direction and then 'hurled racial epithets at them, while punching and kicking them the entire time'.

